notesStmt.note: Title for manuscript and section titles supplied by cataloger.

msContents.summary: Books II (materia medica), III (diseases arranged by part of the body), IV (diseases not specific to particular organs), and V (compound drugs, ointments, and electuaries) of Avicenna's medical encyclopedia. Some marginal notes, beginning in Book III, with more toward the end of the volume; 2 notes in Arabic laid in following f. 144 and f. 275.

msItem.title: Books II-V of al-Qānūn fī al-ṭibb
msItem.author: Avicenna, 980-1037

msItem.title: Book IV, Kita?b al-Amra?d? al-lati? la takhas? bi-?ud?wi?n bi-?aynih, f. 236v
Book V, Kita?b al-Adwiyah al-murakkabah, f. 329r

supportDesc.extent: 367 leaves : 318 x 220 (215 x 138) mm. bound to 318 x 230 mm. +

collation.p: Paper, i (19th-century?) + 367; 46 gatherings alternating between 6 leaves and 10 leaves, with the last gathering lacking one leaf; [1-367], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto. Catchword on each leaf, lower left verso.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 31 long lines, with names of medicines and ailments written in the margins.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh script, except for the final leaves written in nastaʻlīq script (f. 362r-367r).

decoDesc.decoNote: Significant words and phrases in red ink; names of medicines and ailments in red ink in the margins corresponding to words in red in the text.

binding.p: Possibly 19th-century Indian leather, with stamped medallions in green leather overlay.

origin.p: Written in Persia in the 16th or 17th century.

history.provenance: Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Oct. 2001.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2012.
